{"questionId":"13989","questionHtml":"<p>Hence or otherwise, find the obtuse angle formed by the tangent line to <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\"> <mi>f</mi> </math></span> at <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x = 8\"> <mi>x</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mn>8</mn> </math></span> and the tangent line to <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\"> <mi>f</mi> </math></span> at <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x = 2\"> <mi>x</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mn>2</mn> </math></span>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p>recognition of symmetry about <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = x\"> <mi>y</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mi>x</mi> </math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em>eg</em>&nbsp; &nbsp;(2, 8) ⇔ (8, 2)&nbsp;<img src=\"__IMG__/0a784a1ff24661fed33a28db369674e08dd65f97.png\"></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Verdana' , sans-serif;color:black;\">evidence of doubling <strong>their</strong> angle&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong><em> (M1)</em></strong><br></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Verdana' , sans-serif;color:black;\"><em>eg</em>&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"2 \\times 1.03\"> <mn>2</mn> <mo>×</mo> <mn>1.03</mn> </math></span>,&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"2 \\times 59.0\"> <mn>2</mn> <mo>×</mo> <mn>59.0</mn> </math></span></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Verdana' , sans-serif;color:black;\">2.06075, 118.072°</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Verdana' , sans-serif;color:black;\">2.06 (radians)&nbsp; (118 degrees)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1&nbsp; N2</strong></em></span></